name: Document Title: ITP-074-STR-CAMMS-Precast Super T Installation
ITP Description: CAMMS-Precast Super T Installation
ITP approved for use by: VM
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Product to be selected based on the following criteria:
i. minimum compressive strength requirement as the Expoxy beeding is used to ensure the taper plate fullyengaes with the Girder.
ii. Can be applied in IFC specified nominal thickness (1mm)
VERIFYING DOCUMENTS: ConQA Hold Point Release
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: M16 property calss 12.9 Zinc Coated countersunk socket cap screw
VERIFYING DOCUMENTS: ConQA Hold Point Release
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Precast supplier is required to provide the following Quality Assurance documentation for each element, typically this consists of:
i. Certificate of Compliance / Birth Certificate
viii. Record of dimensional measurements to demonstrate compliance with dimensional tolerances of precast and bearing plates
Note: Different revisions of 610 have different clause numbers
Collate: Precast Quality Assurance Documentation so it can be uploaded into Teambinder
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Elastomeric bearings are to be manufactured to the requirements of the IFC Drawings and AS5100.4.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Material for sole plates and bearing retainers shall be of structural grade steel complying with the requirements of AS 3678. All surfaces and edges of sole plates shall be finished smooth and bearing surfaces shall have a maximum out of flatness of 0.4 mm.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Bearing Plates shall be inspected after fixing to girders and prior to the erection of the girders. Ensure the plate and plate orientation are correct
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Re-check that the As-built dimensional tolerances comply with the requirements below:
○ Variation from grade across the width of individual pedestals shall not exceed 1 in 200
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Place the elastomeric bearings to the survey marks to achieve compliance with the IFC Drawings and tolerances.
Record: The elastomeric bearing ID onto the Red-line Drawings or Survey Report
FREQUENCY: Where applicable, each bearing location
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: 200x200x35mm HDPE packers are to be installed in designated recesses on restraining blocks.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Unless otherwise specified, precast elements shall be lifted using the lifting points provided and supported with the top surface uppermost at all times.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Precast elements shall be placed onto the bearings/bearing shims and not released from the crane until sufficiently braced in accordance with the approved temporary works design and/or IFC drawings.
○ The nominal gap between elements is as per the IFC Drawings.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: All manufactured precast elements shall be traced from the completion of manufacture to their final location by a unique identification number.
Record: The final location of each precast element, showing individual ID and date installed onto the Red-line Drawings or Survey Report
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Provide record of dimensional measurements to demonstrate concrete members comply with specified tolerances.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Ensure that any NCRs pertaining to the lot / element / Work area that this ITP covers, have been closed in CAMs.
FREQUENCY: Once, prior to closure of this lot / element / Work area

On behalf of Metropolitan Roads Program Alliance, it is hereby certified that the Works represented by the item of work listed have been tested in accordance with the Project Quality Plan and conform in all respects with the requirements of the Contract.
